        "id": 1398165
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-05T21:39:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Chatted with the Nodir to learn the reason why the `builder` is handled like this. The intention of that code is to ensure only unique value for the builder key. That\u0027s why the error msg says like `builder:xxx` conflicts with tag `builder:xx`. In validation, we allow the duplicate tags to pass and don\u0027t throw the errors. All the tags are eventually placed in a set and duplicates are removed when storing into the DB. So I added a note in this function comment to explain the intention for future developers.  \n\nAs for the `buildset` different `commit/gitiles` value is literally invalid.",
      "parentUuid": "3814d9cf_68fe394d",
      "revId": "ef50a0da9a42da75a328f40b1131d129c1f0b51c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
